revisions.description: The MIB module for performance management.
V4.07 modify MIB nodes hwPMReSetCurrentDataIndicatorID, hwPMReSetCurrentDataInstanceName,hwPMReSetCurrentDataInstanceType for mistakes in format.
V4.06 delete MIB nodes hwPMReSetCurrentDataIndicatorID, hwPMReSetCurrentDataInstanceName,hwPMReSetCurrentDataInstanceType from group as they are undefined or unaccessible.
V4.02 Add hwPMServerVPNType to support VPN.
V3.00, modify for this MIB module.
V1.00, The initial revision of this MIB module.

hwPMStatisticsTaskTable.name: hwPMStatisticsTaskTable
hwPMStatisticsTaskTable.description: The statistics task table, providing create/modify/delete operations. To create a task, you need to create a related record in this table, and add instance nodes in the hwPMTaskInstanceTable. If you delete a task, the related instances in the hwPMTaskInstanceTable will be deleted.

hwPMStatisticsTaskName.name: hwPMStatisticsTaskName

hwPMStatisticsTaskFileFormat.description: The statistics task file format, only text(1) can be supported now.

hwPMStatisticsUploadAutoName.name: hwPMStatisticsUploadAutoName
hwPMStatisticsUploadAutoName.description: The object refers to the mib node hwPMFileUploadRequestName,which enables the device to automatically and periodically send statistics files to the server.

hwPMStatisticsHighPrecisionPeriod.name: hwPMStatisticsHighPrecisionPeriod
hwPMStatisticsHighPrecisionPeriod.description: The interval of statistics task, in seconds. if taskType is sdhShort , It must be multiple of 5 seconds and less or equal to 900 seconds, else It must be multiple of 30 seconds.

hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdTriggerAlarm.name: hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdTriggerAlarm
hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdTriggerAlarm.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an alarm entry crosses its rising threshold and generates an event that is configured for sending SNMP traps. When alarm is high trigger, hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdType is 1, when alarm is low trigger, hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdType is 2.

hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdClearAlarm.name: hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdClearAlarm
hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdClearAlarm.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an alarm entry crosses its falling threshold and generates an event that is configured for sending SNMP traps. When alarm is high trigger, hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdType is 1, when alarm is low trigger, hwPMStatisticsTaskThresholdType is 2.

hwPMFileUploadFileList.name: hwPMFileUploadFileList
hwPMFileUploadFileList.description: The file list needed to be uploaded. Format is TaskName1:FileIndex1,TaskName2:FileIndex2.

hwPMFileUploadStatus.name: hwPMFileUploadStatus
hwPMFileUploadStatus.description: The file upload status. init(1): FTP has not been starting to upload file. running(2): FTP is running. If you set this node as running, the FTP will be started. success(3): FTP completed successfully. fileOpenFail(4): FTP failed. The cause is file open failure. unreachableServerIp(5): FTP failed. The cause is that the IP address of the server is not reachable. linkFailed(6): FTP failed. The cause is connecting to server failed. authenticateFailed(7): FTP failed. The cause is authenticating failed.For FTP mode only. fileReadFailed(8): FTP failed. The cause is reading file failed. fileWriteFailed(9): FTP failed. The cause is writing file failed. failed(10):FTP failed, General error.
